<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>In both validation components a filter instance is used without configuration besides allowWhitespace.</p>

<p>So when unicode is enabled they both perform a preg match with unicode letter and number properties. So testing against a real alphanumeric string isnt possible..</p>

<p>Maybe make it so that alnum tests by default on the english alphabet, and alpha like it does in the current form.</p>

